1. config jmeter to make it log response data in command line mode
	1. generate jmx file in gui mode
	2. specify "Functional Test Mode" to true on the Test Plan element in jmx file or check the checkbox of Functional Test Mode in gui mode
	3. set the property of jmeter.save.saveservice.output_format=xml in jmeter.properties
2. config jmeter to use proxy server in gui mode
	1. set the http request implementation to Java for sample
	2. set proxy server info, for example:
		Server Name or IP: proxy_server_name
		Port number: port_number
		User Name: user_name
		Password: password of user
